just_use feature_weight.py

# label: SPIKE (code-analysis tool)
# role: agent tool — measure a feature's footprint via grep patterns

Walks the repo counting lines that match one or more regex
patterns, classifying each hit file into three tiers:

- **OWNED_BY_PATH** — path matches the pattern (definitionally
  owned, regardless of content).
- **OWNED_BY_CONTENT** — focus ratio (matches / file LOC)
  meets `--focus-threshold` (default 10%).
- **REFERENCING** — has matches but below the focus bar.

Useful when estimating "how big is feature X" without
maintaining manual scope lists.

## Status (TENTATIVE)

Labeled SPIKE because usage has been occasional; I haven't
verified it runs clean against the current repo layout or
that the thresholds still feel right. The classification
bands (PATH / CONTENT / REFERENCING) are the interesting
part — the rest is a grep wrapper.

## Surface

- `python3 tools/feature_weight.py [OPTIONS] PATTERN [PATTERN ...]`
- `--exclude REGEX` — skip paths (e.g. drop vendored or
  mirrored code).
- `--focus-threshold PCT` — cutoff for
  CONTENT-vs-REFERENCING.

## Pointers

- Related tool: `tools/pain_rank.py` — different lens,
  similar read-only quantitative style.
